{"lemma":"بَرْبَرٍ","slug":"بَرْبَرٍ","root":"ب.ر.ب.ر","root_slug":"ب-ر-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2142","n2153","n2154","n2155"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Berber","tags":["ethnic","offensive","slur"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"uncivilized, wild"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"animal, bestial, beastly, brutal, feral"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ruthless, savage, barbaric, barbarous"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"inhumane, inhuman"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Berber","tags":["ethnic","offensive","slur"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"barbarian, savage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ruffian"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"بَرْبَر (barbar, “Berbers”) + ـِيّ (-iyy), probably from Ancient Greek βάρβαρος (bárbaros, “non-Greek, foreign, barbarian”), apparently imitative of foreign speech."},"ipa":["/bar.ba.rijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2142","headword_ar":"بَرْبَرَ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobarapN","text_ar":"بَرْبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He talked much, and raised a clamour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused noise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his tongue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cried out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and talked in anger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talked confusedly, with anger and aversion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobara fiY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"بَرْبَرَ فِى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was profuse and unprofitable in his talk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) ―         -b2-  Also, inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a goat)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered a cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rattled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being excited by desire of the female."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n2153","headword_ar":"بَرْبَرُ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albarobaru","text_ar":"البَرْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) [a coll. gen. proper name, of which the n. un., or rel. n., is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobariY~N","text_ar":"بَرْبَرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] a foreign word, (S,) [probably of African origin, the primary form of which is the source of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"βάρβαρος","text_ar":"βάρβαρος","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,] arabicized; (Msb;) or, as some say, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobarapN","text_ar":"بَرْبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in speech; (TA; [see R. Q. 1;]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaraAbirapu","text_ar":"البَرَابِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobaru","text_ar":"بَرْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albarobaru","text_ar":"البَرْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobariY~N","text_ar":"بَرْبَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with what follows and with analogy,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added because the sing. is a foreign word, or [so in the M and TA, but in the S “ and, ”] a rel. n., (S, M,) but it may be elided; [so that one may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaraAbiru","text_ar":"البَرَابِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the inhabitants of El-Maghrib"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Northern Africa west of Egypt"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh, * Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the Arabs of the desert in hardness, and coarseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rudeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, * Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in slightness of religion, and littleness of knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Colobi"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by Diodorus Siculus and Strabo,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the Abyssinians and the Zinj, who amputate"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the glans of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the penis, and make it a dowry for a wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [There are various opinions of the origins of these races. The appellation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaraAbirapu","text_ar":"البَرَابِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sing. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobariY~N","text_ar":"بَرْبَرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is also applied by late historians, and in the present day, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The races inhabiting the portion of the valley of the Nile which we commonly call Nubia."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Mgh","Msb","M"]},{"entry_id":"n2154","headword_ar":"بُرْبُرٌ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barobaArN","text_ar":"بَرْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2155","headword_ar":"بِرْبِرٌ","root":"br","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bir~N","text_ar":"بِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%B1/","headword_ar":"بربر","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_12","lexicon_en":"Al-Muṭarrizī, al-Mughrib fī Tartīb al-Muʿrib (d. 1213 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المغرب في ترتيب المعرب للمُطَرِّزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22037#53340f","body_html":"(الْبَرْبَرُ) قَوْمٌ بِالْمَغْرِبِ جُفَاةٌ كَالْأَعْرَابِ فِي رِقَّةِ الدِّينِ وَقِلَّةِ الْعِلْمِ."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_13","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣaghānī, al-Shawārid (d. 1252 CE)","lexicon_ar":"الشوارد للصغاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22037#88621a","body_html":"<span>(بربر) : البُرْبُر: الكثيِرٌ الأَصْواتِ. </span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_51","lexicon_en":"Habib Anthony Salmone, An Advanced Learner's Arabic-English Dictionary (1889)","lexicon_ar":"حبيب سالمون، قاموس عربي انجليزي متقدم للمتعلمين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22037#3d6c3e","body_html":"بربر<br> بَرْبَرَ<br> a. Talked indistinctly.<br> <br> بَرْبَاْرa. Loquacious, jabberer.<br> <br> بَرْبَر<br> (pl.<br> بَرَاْبِرَة)<br>a. Berbers.<br> <br> بَرْبَرِيَّةa. Barbary."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_21","lexicon_en":"Muḥammad al-Fattinī, Majmaʿ Biḥār al-Anwār fī Gharāʾib al-Tanzīl wa Laṭāʾif al-Akhbār (d. 1578 CE)","lexicon_ar":"مجمع بحار الأنوار للفَتِّنيّ","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22037#083e02","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">[بربر]</span><span> نه فيه: طلبوا تحليل الربا والخمر فامتنع فقاموا ولهم تغذمر و\"بربرة\" البربرة التخليط في الكلام مع غضب ونفور، وبربر فعله. ومنه: أخذ اللواء غلام أسود فنصبه و\"بربر\".</span>"}]}}